06:03.029 --> 06:04.865
<i>‐ I'm spending the time</i>
<i>to clean the steel.</i>

06:04.865 --> 06:07.659
I'm probably spending a lot
of time, maybe too much time,

06:07.659 --> 06:11.371
and I'm just hoping that what
I'm doing is the correct route.

06:11.371 --> 06:14.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:14.708 --> 06:16.376
<i>‐ I got a bar</i>
<i>of hardenable steel,</i>

06:16.376 --> 06:17.711
<i>I flattened it out,</i>

06:17.711 --> 06:20.046
<i>stick it between</i>
<i>my two pieces of mild steel,</i>

06:20.046 --> 06:22.549
and toss it in the forge,
get it welding.

06:22.549 --> 06:25.802
‐ Garrett's got a stack
about three by four.

06:25.802 --> 06:28.388
It's great, he's only got
a 4‐inch weld to worry about.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.056
It's a good way to start out.

06:30.056 --> 06:32.225
‐ This initial press is
what's gonna make or break

06:32.225 --> 06:34.603
